      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): pass visitedDirectories to all discoverInDirectory calls to fix infinite statx loop",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #86780 — `openclaw status --json` enters an infinite statx loop consuming 100% CPU and never exiting.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`discoverOpenClawPlugins` initializes `visitedDirectories` in two separate scopes but never passes it to the `discoverInDirectory` call sites. With optional-chaining guards (`?.has` / `?.add`) silently no-oping on `undefined`, cycle detection was fully disabled.\n\nWhen `recurseDirectories=true`, `discoverInDirectory` recursively calls itself with `...params` spread — which would propagate `visitedDirectories` if present, but since it was never initialized at the call sites, every recursive call re-scanned the same 95 directories indefinitely (~26,000 statx calls/sec).\n\nThe 2026-05-22 `deriveIdHint` fix (#85170) stripped the `-plugin` suffix so directories that previously hit an early `continue` now fell through to the `recurseDirectories` branch, triggering the latent bug.\n\n## Fix\n\nInitialize `visitedDirectories = new Set<string>()` in both the `scoped` and `shared` discovery scopes inside `discoverOpenClawPlugins`, and pass it to all 6 `discoverInDirectory` call sites.\n\n- 6 insertions, 0 deletions\n- No function signature changes\n- No behavior change for non-recursive scans\n\n## Testing\n\n- `tsc --noEmit` passes with no errors\n- The `visitedDirectories` dedup set now correctly prevents revisiting symlinked or repeated directories during recursive plugin discovery",
        "branch": "fix/discovery-visitedDirectories-infinite-loop",
        "head_sha": "7caaa1d55786665d3b9c7c2292f971231f10fce5",
